\f0\b Objective:
\f1\b0  To find the CDF and PDF of a new transformed random variable, $f_Y(y)$.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b General PDF Transformation Formula:
\f1\b0  For a transformation, the PDF is defined by the following equation:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$f_Y(y) = \\frac\{f_X(x)\}\{|\\frac\{dy\}\{dx\}|\}\\Bigg|_\{x=g^\{-1\}(y)\}$$\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

