\f0\b Derivation for a Monotonically Increasing Transformation:
\f1\b0 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Step 1 ($S_1$):
\f1\b0  Establish the CDF.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$F_Y(y) = Pr(Y \\le y) = Pr(g(x) \\le y)$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 By using the inverse $x = g^\{-1\}(y)$, the expression becomes:\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +1
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 $$F_\{PDF\} = Pr(x \\le g^\{-1\}(y)) = F_X(g^\{-1\}(y))$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Step 2 ($S_2$):
\f1\b0  Differentiate with respect to $y$.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$f_Y(y) = \\frac\{d\}\{dy\}[F_X(g^\{-1\}(y))]$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Applying the chain rule yields:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$f_Y(y) = f_X(g^\{-1\}(y)) \\cdot \\frac\{d\}\{dy\}g^\{-1\}(y) = f_X(x) \\frac\{dx\}\{dy\}\\Bigg|_\{x=g^\{-1\}(y)\}$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Derivation for a Decreasing Transformation:
\f1\b0 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Step 1 ($S_1$):
\f1\b0  Establish the CDF considering the decreasing nature.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$F_Y(y) = Pr(Y \\le y) = Pr(X \\ge g^\{-1\}(y)) = 1 - F_X(g^\{-1\}(y))$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Step 2 ($S_2$):
\f1\b0  Differentiate the CDF.\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +1
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 $$f_Y(y) = 0 - f_X(x)\\frac\{dx\}\{dy\}\\Bigg|_\{x=g^\{-1\}(y)\}$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f0\b Step 3 ($S_3$):
\f1\b0  Change the limits for $y$.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
