\f0\b Detailed Derivation for the Case $Z = X + Y$:
\f1\b0 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 By isolating variables, we establish $Y = Z - X$ and $X = Z - Y$.\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +2
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The cumulative distribution function for $Z$ is:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 $$F_Z(z) = Pr(Z \\le z) = Pr(X + Y \\le z)$$\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The region is integrated using a strip with respect to the joint distribution $f_\{X,Y\}(x,y) dy dx$.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
